<p><b>What is my role in protecting the personal information of the parties to the dispute?</b></p>
<p>If you are the applicant or are representing the applicant, you are responsible for entering into the dispute management system the correct and up-to-date contact information for all parties to the dispute, including correct mailing addresses and email addresses.</p>
<p>You must make every reasonable effort to enter the correct contact information for all parties. If you enter incorrect contact information, then there is a risk that the personal information of the parties may be inadvertently shared with the wrong recipient.</p>
<p>By entering or viewing contact information in the dispute management system you agree and represent that the contact information entered or viewed is correct to the best of your knowledge. You agree that you will notify the RTB immediately if any of the parties' contact information changes or if you become aware of incorrect contact information.</p>


